external_knowledge:
- 'voyages' are metaphorical references to the experiments;
- 'spectators' are users with 'read-only' permission, implying they can observe but not alter the experiment;
- 'stories' refer to the descriptions of the experiments;
- 'aliases' are usernames of users;
- 'latest expeditions' mean experiments created most recently.

sql:
SELECT eu.user_id, COUNT(eu.experiment_id) AS number_of_experiments
FROM experiment_user eu
GROUP BY eu.user_id;

